e relationship with developments in medicine, health, and disease, highlighting the perplexing dual nature of the drug as both the cause and relief of great suffering in widely diverse civilizations.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 0aOpium -- History. 0aOpium abuse -- History. 0aOpium abusexHistory. 0aOpium trade -- History. 0aOpium tradexHistory. 0aOpiumxHistory. 7aHISTORY / Social History.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertYale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311053799440uhttps://doi.org/10.12987/978030018365840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780300183658423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780300183658/original  a978-3-11-053799-4  Yale University Press Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aEBA_FAO  aEBA_UCA_YUP  aGBV-deGruyter-alles